[src:aws-x-ray/observability] In fact, it is not possible to distinguish the initial state for $x_{1}$ from that of $x_{2}$ if $x_{1}-x_{2}$ is in the null space of $M(t_{0},t_{1})$ .
[src:aws-x-ray/observability] The system is observable in $[t_{0},t_{1}]$ if and only if there exists an interval $[t_{0},t_{1}]$ in $\mathbb {R}$ such that the matrix $M(t_{0},t_{1})$ is nonsingular.
